Etymology. – The species is named in honour of our colleague Peter Phillipson who obtained funds and arranged the first field mission to Beanka in 2009 and contributed to the floristic checklist recently published on the region ( GAUTIER & al., 2013 ). Peter has collected over 3000 plants in Madagascar , especially in the dry south-western region where he first collected in 1987. He has a wide knowledge on many plant groups on the Island and participates actively in the milestone “Catalogue of the Vascular plants of Madagascar ” project (
MADAGASCAR CATALOGUE, 2014
).
